<!-- END CLASS="ROW" -->
<div class="row">
      <div class="twelve columns">
            <div class="storytitle">
                  <h1>Sandwich Monday: The Grilled Cheese Doughnut</h1>
         <input type="hidden" id="title163395736" value="Sandwich Monday: The Grilled Cheese Doughnut"></input>
         <input type="hidden" id="modelShortUrl163395736" value="http://n.pr/TsNx7i"></input>
         <input type="hidden" id="modelFullUrl163395736" value="http://www.npr.org/blogs/thesalt/2012/10/22/163395736/sandwich-monday-the-grilled-cheese-donut"></input>
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="STORYTITLE" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END CLASS="TWELVE COLUMNS" -->
</div>

<!-- END CLASS="ROW" -->
<div class="row">
      <div class="twelve columns">
            <div id="story-meta">
                  <div id="storybyline" class="  linkLocation">
                        <div class="bucketwrap byline" id="res163395738">
                              <p class="byline">by <span>Ian Chillag</span></p>
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETWRAP BYLINE" ID="RES163395738" PREVIEWTITLE="BYLINES" -->
         </div>
         
<!-- END ID="STORYBYLINE" CLASS="  LINKLOCATION" -->
         <div class="dateblock">
                        <time datetime="2012-10-22"><span class="date">October 22, 2012</span><span class="time"> 1:07 PM</span></time>
         </div>
      </div>
      
<!-- END ID="STORY-META" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END CLASS="TWELVE COLUMNS" -->
</div>

<!-- END CLASS="ROW" -->
<div class="row">
      <div class="twelve columns">
            <div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation">
                  <div id="res163401259" class="bucketwrap image large">
                        <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-2-7--daa4239b9de0936c7fa0b515af7a892507fefa99-s6-c10.jpg" data-original="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-2-7--daa4239b9de0936c7fa0b515af7a892507fefa99.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  title="The Gronut." alt="The Gronut." />            <div class="captionwrap">
                              <div class="caption">
                                    <p>The Gronut.</p>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTION" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTIONWRAP" -->
            <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>            <a href="#" class="enlargebtn" title="Enlarge">i</a>            <div class="enlarge_measure">
                              <div class="img_wrap">
                                    <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-2-7--daa4239b9de0936c7fa0b515af7a892507fefa99-s51.jpg" title="The Gronut." alt="The Gronut." />
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMG_WRAP" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_MEASURE" -->
            <div class="enlarge_html">
                              <div class="image_data">
                                    <p class="caption">The Gronut.</p>                   <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMAGE_DATA" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_HTML" -->
         </div>
         <p>Celebrity couples always get our attention: Kim &amp; Kanye, Brangelina, Gosling &amp; Totenberg. The Grilled Cheese Doughnut is just such a pairing: Two titans together as one. We'll call it Gronut.</p>         <div id="res163401448" class="bucketwrap image large">
                        <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-4-1--81185af2231d223c290bc63e88d01f69c21271fb-s6-c10.jpg" data-original="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-4-1--81185af2231d223c290bc63e88d01f69c21271fb.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  title="A cross section." alt="A cross section." />            <div class="captionwrap">
                              <div class="caption">
                                    <p>A cross section.</p>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTION" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTIONWRAP" -->
            <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>            <a href="#" class="enlargebtn" title="Enlarge">i</a>            <div class="enlarge_measure">
                              <div class="img_wrap">
                                    <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-4-1--81185af2231d223c290bc63e88d01f69c21271fb-s51.jpg" title="A cross section." alt="A cross section." />
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMG_WRAP" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_MEASURE" -->
            <div class="enlarge_html">
                              <div class="image_data">
                                    <p class="caption">A cross section.</p>                   <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMAGE_DATA" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_HTML" -->
         </div>
         <p>Take a glazed doughnut, slice it open, flip both halves around so they're cut-side out, slap on some cheese, and grill it in butter. We think Ohio's <a href="http://www.tomandchee.com/">Tom &amp; Chee Restaurant</a> did it first, and we're guessing they did a better job than we did.</p>         <p><strong>Ian</strong>: Ew. I think the proper pronunciation here is "grilled cheese DO NOT."</p>         <p><strong>Blythe</strong>: It's a panono.</p>         <p><strong>Eva</strong>: Doughnuts are so versatile! No bread? Make a doughnut grilled cheese! No milk? Pour donuts on your cereal!</p>         <p><strong>Ian</strong>: What could be more American than this? If they really want to look like men of the people, I think President Obama and Governor Romney should wear these on their lapels tonight.</p>         <p><strong>Leah</strong>: It's nice to think that all the cheese in my arteries will have a flotation device.</p>         <div id="res163401020" class="bucketwrap image large">
                        <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-1-7--e5fbc3ebfed02faf8e15888c4b2660ee6b1121e3-s6-c10.jpg" data-original="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-1-7--e5fbc3ebfed02faf8e15888c4b2660ee6b1121e3.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  title="In process." alt="In process." />            <div class="captionwrap">
                              <div class="caption">
                                    <p>In process.</p>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTION" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTIONWRAP" -->
            <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>            <a href="#" class="enlargebtn" title="Enlarge">i</a>            <div class="enlarge_measure">
                              <div class="img_wrap">
                                    <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-1-7--e5fbc3ebfed02faf8e15888c4b2660ee6b1121e3-s51.jpg" title="In process." alt="In process." />
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMG_WRAP" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_MEASURE" -->
            <div class="enlarge_html">
                              <div class="image_data">
                                    <p class="caption">In process.</p>                   <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMAGE_DATA" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_HTML" -->
         </div>
         <p><strong>Ian</strong>: Looking through the doughnut hole is like looking through a little window to the inside of me. It's all melted cheese in there, too.</p>         <p><strong>Blythe</strong>: This Kraft Single is more like Kraft Single-with-seven-cats.</p>         <p><strong>Eva</strong>: A word of warning: do not dunk this in coffee.</p>         <p><strong>Robert</strong>: Goes great with the insulinccino though.</p>         <p>[The verdict: it's possible we made an error using American cheese, but this wasn't very good. We'll keep trying until we get it right, or at least until we have to buy new pants.]</p>         <div id="res163401202" class="bucketwrap image large">
                        <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-1-9--5b3a93dd8cbd8b190730d7c826fd6db301837aa5-s6-c10.jpg" data-original="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-1-9--5b3a93dd8cbd8b190730d7c826fd6db301837aa5.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  title="Robert does not approve." alt="Robert does not approve." />            <div class="captionwrap">
                              <div class="caption">
                                    <p>Robert does not approve.</p>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTION" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="CAPTIONWRAP" -->
            <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>            <a href="#" class="enlargebtn" title="Enlarge">i</a>            <div class="enlarge_measure">
                              <div class="img_wrap">
                                    <img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/10/22/photo-1-9--5b3a93dd8cbd8b190730d7c826fd6db301837aa5-s51.jpg" title="Robert does not approve." alt="Robert does not approve." />
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMG_WRAP" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_MEASURE" -->
            <div class="enlarge_html">
                              <div class="image_data">
                                    <p class="caption">Robert does not approve.</p>                   <span class="creditwrap"><span class="rightsnotice">NPR</span></span>
               </div>
               
<!-- END CLASS="IMAGE_DATA" -->
            </div>
            
<!-- END CLASS="ENLARGE_HTML" -->
         </div>
         <p><em><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/archives/archive.php?thingId=126351221">Sandwich Monday</a> is a regular feature from the staff of "Wait, Wait...Don't Tell Me..." Sandwich Monday has no nutritional or educational value whatsoever, may cause heartburn, and it's possible that reading it will make your eyes fat.</em></p>
